# 2026-05-07 12:59:34.752908
+Build a tiered model routing stack for the home-ai system with the following layers:
+
+**Tier 1 – Local fast (default):** Ollama running locally. Use the best available 
+model (prefer qwen2.5:7b or phi4:14b). Endpoint: http://localhost:11434. Use for 
+routine classification, summarisation, short generation, and internal tool calls 
+where latency matters.
+
+**Tier 2 – Local capable:** Ollama with llama3.3:70b. Use for tasks requiring 
+stronger reasoning but where cloud escalation is undesirable — sensitive data, 
+offline operation, or cost control.
+
+**Tier 3 – DeepSeek V3 via API:** Use for complex multi-step reasoning, long-context 
+tasks, and code generation where local models are struggling. Endpoint via 
+DeepSeek's OpenAI-compatible API (https://api.deepseek.com/v1). Model string: 
+deepseek-chat.
+
+**Tier 4 – Claude (escalation ceiling):** Anthropic API, claude-sonnet-4-20250514. 
+Use only when lower tiers fail, timeout, or produce low-confidence output. Also 
+used for任务 requiring tool use with complex JSON schemas.
+
+Requirements:
+- Router lives in /home_ai/core/model_router.py
+- Accepts: prompt, task_type (enum: classify|generate|reason|code|embed), 
+  max_tier (1-4, default 4), context_length, and optional confidence_threshold
+- Returns: response text, model used, tier used, latency_ms
+- Routing logic: attempt tier 1 first; escalate if response is empty, contains 
+  an apology/refusal pattern, latency exceeds threshold, or confidence_score 
+  (if available) is below threshold
+- All credentials loaded from environment variables (DEEPSEEK_API_KEY, 
+  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY) — never hardcoded
+- Async throughout (asyncio/httpx)
+- Structured logging to match existing home-ai log format
+- Unit tests in /home_ai/tests/test_model_router.py covering each tier 
+  and escalation paths
+
+Do not use LangChain or LlamaIndex. Implement direct API calls only.

